    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>N.J. TRANSIT FARES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Karen Demasters</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Jersey Transit plans to find ways to make up $39 million loss in state funding without raising bus and train fares (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>New Jersey Transit says it will find ways to make up a $39 million loss in state funding other than raising fares for bus and train riders. Fares have not been raised in 10 years. The cuts, in transit operating money, came in the latest state budget last month. The agency will seek money from other state and federal sources, a spokesman said.</p>
        <p>Karen DeMasters</p>
      </block>
